Privacy Statement for Asahi Kasei SMS Notification Service
This Privacy Policy explains how Asahi Kasei collects, uses, stores, and protects personal data associated with the SMS on‑call and incident‑notification service. This service is intended solely for internal operational communication.
1. Data Collected
When you opt in to receive SMS notifications, Asahi Kasei collects and processes the following information:

Mobile phone number
Name and internal user identifier (if required for routing or verification)
Message delivery metadata (timestamps, delivery status)

No additional profile, behavioral, or location data is collected through this SMS service.
2. Purpose of Data Use
Your data is used exclusively to:

Deliver internal operational SMS alerts
Notify you about urgent IT or on‑call incidents
Support secure and reliable service delivery
Maintain audit and traceability controls in accordance with Asahi Kasei Group personal‑information management policies [AK Group P...les_ALL_EN | PDF]

Your data will not be sold, shared externally, or used for marketing.
3. Data Storage & Security
Asahi Kasei applies group‑wide security and personal‑information management systems, including:

Appointed responsible persons for personal‑information oversight
Internal rules and policies consistent with legal requirements
Continuous monitoring, evaluation, and mitigation of privacy risks

All SMS data is stored securely within authorized systems and retained only as long as necessary for operational continuity and compliance.
4. Opt‑In & Opt‑Out
Participation in SMS alerts is voluntary.

To stop receiving messages: reply STOP
To receive support: reply HELP

5. How to Contact Us
For questions about how your data is used, or to exercise privacy rights, you can contact the Asahi Kasei IT Service Desk:

Email: it.servicedesk@asahi-kasei.com
Phone: +33 12 34 56 78

6. Publicly Accessible URL
This Privacy Policy is available at the following publicly accessible link:
https://www.asahi-kasei.com/privacy/
